---
import AppLayout from "../layouts/AppLayout.astro";
---

<AppLayout
  title="Bore v2 workspace"
  description="Phase 3 web foundation is complete for Bore v2."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Phase 3 complete</p>
      <h2>Typed browser flows are now wired into the real v2 API lane.</h2>
      <p>
        This repo still ships the Go relay, CLI, legacy <code>web/</code>, and
        <code>tui/</code> as v1. The v2 lane under <code>apps/</code> and
        <code>packages/</code> now goes beyond route placeholders by creating,
        loading, joining, and summarizing real PostgreSQL-backed sessions.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="panel">
      <h3>What exists now</h3>
      <ul class="stack-list">
        <li>Root Bun workspace for the v2 rewrite</li>
        <li>Elysia API with durable session and operator-summary endpoints</li>
        <li>Astro + Vue pages for send, receive, and ops flows</li>
        <li>Shared Zod contracts plus a typed browser API client</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="panel-grid">
    <article class="panel">
      <h3>Send</h3>
      <p>
        Create a real session from the browser and get a verified rendezvous code
        back from the v2 API.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="/send">Open send shell</a>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <h3>Receive</h3>
      <p>
        Dynamic receive routes now load typed session state and let a receiver join
        the waiting shell.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="/receive/demo-code">Open receive shell</a>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <h3>Ops</h3>
      <p>
        The ops route now shows health and live v2 operator summary data without the
        legacy Go <code>/status</code> dependency.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="/ops">Open ops shell</a>
    </article>
  </section>
</AppLayout>
